news.title: Andhra Pradesh RERA directs CRDA to pay interest for flat allottees
news.para: The APRERA directed the APCRDA to pay the interest from June 30, 2022 till the time the flats are handed over to the allottees. The interest rate was decided as the Prime Lending Rate of State Bank of India + 2%.

news.title: Gurgram builder jumps from balcony to evade CBI arrest, fractures leg
news.para: A team of CBI had gone to his house to arrest with a warrant when Sanjiv Kumar, the accused, jumped from the balcony, said police.

news.title: Notices issued as per demarcation report of government: DDA
news.para: The DDA's submissions were made in an affidavit filed in response to a petition by a group of residents in Mehrauli, whose properties, along with various other properties, have been identified to be demolished as part of the 'anti-encroachment' drive.

news.title: One lakh housing units for poor in 2023-24 under PMAY: Haryana CM
news.para: Khattar said the government targeted to complete the allocation in the next financial year. For this purpose, the budget has allocated Rs 5,893 crore under project of housing for the poor.

news.title: Builder of affordable houses has to pay for upkeep of roads, parks: DTCP
news.para: This comes after homebuyers of affordable housing projects complained that developers are collecting upkeep fees ranging between Rs 2.50 and Rs 4 per sq ft from them in violation of the Affordable Housing Policy 2013.

news.title: In China, more families on the fence on home buying, foreclosures cloud sector
news.para: But more households were considering buying a home or investing in other assets in the coming three months, according to the survey by a research institute and think tank under Ant Group and the Southwestern University of Finance and Economics released on Wednesday.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh makes special allocation for metro rail projects in Agra, Kanpur in Budget 2023
news.para: ​"A budgetary provision of Rs 585 crore made for the Kanpur Metro Rail Project and provision of Rs 465 crore made for the Agra Metro Rail Project," a statement issued by the government said.

news.title: Punjab vigilance bureau arrests real estate operator in Kharar over Rs 2.22 crore in dues
news.para: Parveen Kumar, the accused, had bought six acres of land in village Khanpur in 2018 and built the colony, a spokesperson of the bureau said. For getting the maps and plans passed of this colony, he deposited only Rs 6,58,213, out of total dues of Rs 2,02,51,105.

news.title: Arvind Subramanian resigns as MD & CEO of Mahindra Lifespace Developers
news.para: The board also approved appointment of Amit Kumar Sinha as managing director (Designate) of Mahindra Lifespace Developers from February 23, 2023 to May 22, 2023. From May 23, 2023, he will take over as full time MD & CEO for a period of five years.

news.title: Indore civic body removes 75 illegal structures on government land
news.para: IMC commissioner Pratibha Pal has instructed officials concerned to identify and take appropriate action against illegal colonies.

news.title: Property prices in 50 cities increase by 7.1% year-on-year in Q3 FY23: NHB Residex
news.para: All the eight major metros of the country viz., Ahmedabad (14.4%), Bengaluru (8.0%), Chennai (8.7%), Delhi (1.8%), Hyderabad (10.2%), Kolkata (7.4%), Mumbai (4.4%) & Pune (7.2%) recorded increase in the index on an annual basis.

news.title: Dubai housing boom buoys buyers, burdens tenants
news.para: Dubai, renowned for its towering skyscrapers and ultra-luxury villas, saw record real estate transactions in 2022, largely due to the influx of wealthy investors -- especially from Russia.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board removes illegal structures in sector 45, 46
news.para: The CHB is computing cost of demolitions that will be recovered from the allottees and in case of its non-payment their allotments are liable to be cancelled.

news.title: Indore development body gives nod to two new residential schemes
news.para: The board meeting led by chairman Jaypal Singh Chawda and attended Indore collector Ilayaraja T, Indore Municipal Corporation commissioner Pratibha Pal and the authority CEO RP Ahirwar held a discussion over five agendas.

news.title: 'Stilt-plus-four-floors' building policy in abeyance across Haryana: CM
news.para: The government has also announced that a committee would also be constituted to re-examine the issue and till the findings of the committee, there will be complete stay on permissions for construction of four-storey floors in the residential sectors of the state.
